  "id": "hisn-114",
  "title": "What to do if you have a bad dream or nightmare",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 114",
  "arabic": "يَنْفُثُ عَنْ يَسَارِهِ ثلاثاً يَسْتَعِيذُ بِاللَّهِ مِنَ الشَّيطَانِ وَمِنْ شَرِّ مَا رَأَى ثَلاَثَ مَرَّاتٍ لاَ يُحَدِّثْ بِهَا أَحَداً يَتَحَوَّلُ عَنْ جَنْبِهِ الَّذِي كَانَ عَلَيْهِ",
  "meaning": "[((Spit on your left three times)(Spit: A form of spitting comprising mainly of air with little spittle)) - (Seek refuge in Allah from shaytan and the evil of what you saw (Three Times)) - (Do not relate it to anyone) - (Turn and sleep on the opposite side to which you were sleeping on previously.) - (Get up and pray if you so desire.) ]",
